The man who shot dead the Russian ambassador to Ankara on Monday has been identified as a Turkish policeman, the city&#8217;s mayor said.&#8220;The attacker is a policeman,&#8221; Melih Gokcek said on his official Twitter account, after numerous reports on social media identifying the gunman, who was smartly dressed in a suit and tie.The Yeni Safak daily said on its website that the attacker &#8212; named as M.M.A. &#8212; worked with anti-riot police in Ankara.-AFP